    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="989"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d989">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/7–3145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 31, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>725. Department’s 397, July 30, 7 p.m.<note n="5" xml:id="d989fn5">Not printed;
                        it requested comment on the agenda, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                    Embassy approves proposed agenda. The former administration of the Government of
                    Panama expressed the desire to hold staff conferences, however the new
                        administration<note n="6" xml:id="d989fn6">President Enrique A. Jimenez took
                        office after his election by the Second National Constituent Assembly, June
                        15, 1945.</note> has not been consulted which General Brett and I feel
                    should be done before any further action is taken in this regard. Does the
                    Department agree?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Donnelly</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
